  bits=7: scores=(np.int64(0), np.int64(1), np.int64(2)), H=1, betti=[np.int64(1), np.int64(0), np.int64(0)], omega=[3, 3, 1]

======================================================================
SUMMARY: Higher Betti and H-maximization
======================================================================
n | beta_{n-3} | relation to H-max?
3 | beta_0     | trivially 1 always
4 | beta_1     | = 1 iff has 3-cycle (= H > 1)
5 | beta_2     | always 0 (PROVED)
6 | beta_3     | = 1 iff H = max in score class (320/32768)
7 | beta_4     | = 6 iff H = 189 (Paley class, global max among regular)

Pattern: beta_{n-3} > 0 picks out H-maximizers!
But beta_2 = 0 breaks the sequence at n=5...

Alternative: beta_{2*floor((n-1)/2)} > 0 picks out H-maximizers?
n=3: beta_2 = 0 (transitive) or beta_2 = 0 (3-cycle)... no
n=6: beta_3 = beta_{2*2} = beta_4? No, beta_3

Or: the HIGHEST nonzero even Betti (after beta_0)?
n=3: beta_0=1 always
n=5: beta_0=1 always, all even betti = 0
n=6: beta_0=1, beta_2=0, beta_4=0. Odd: beta_1,beta_3
n=7: beta_0=1, beta_2=0, beta_4=6 or 0, beta_6=0
